readStringLength

private static int readStringLength(InputStream input)
                             throws IOException
Calculates the length of the next string to be read. The file is encoded using the c# String format. The length is encoded as an integer, which is read 8 bits at time. The MSb indicates whether the Integer needs another byte of data, 1 if true, 0 if not. The other 7 bits are part (or all) of the integers value. For more information see C# readString

Parameters:
input - Stream of Binary Data.
Returns:
The length of the next string to be read.
Throws:
IOException
